comment:
* A data kind representing the contact's proper name. You can use all * columns defined for {@link ContactsContract.Data} as well as the following aliases. * *

Column aliases

* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
TypeAliasData column
String{@link #DISPLAY_NAME}{@link #DATA1}
String{@link #GIVEN_NAME}{@link #DATA2}
String{@link #FAMILY_NAME}{@link #DATA3}
String{@link #PREFIX}{@link #DATA4}Common prefixes in English names are "Mr", "Ms", "Dr" etc.
String{@link #MIDDLE_NAME}{@link #DATA5}
String{@link #SUFFIX}{@link #DATA6}Common suffixes in English names are "Sr", "Jr", "III" etc.
String{@link #PHONETIC_GIVEN_NAME}{@link #DATA7}Used for phonetic spelling of the name, e.g. Pinyin, Katakana, Hiragana
String{@link #PHONETIC_MIDDLE_NAME}{@link #DATA8}
String{@link #PHONETIC_FAMILY_NAME}{@link #DATA9}

variables.name: CONTENT_ITEM_TYPE
variables.comment: MIME type used when storing this in data table.

variables.name: DISPLAY_NAME
variables.comment:
* The name that should be used to display the contact. * Unstructured component of the name should be consistent with * its structured representation. *

* Type: TEXT

variables.name: GIVEN_NAME
variables.comment:
* The given name for the contact. *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: FAMILY_NAME
variables.comment:
* The family name for the contact. *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: PREFIX
variables.comment:
* The contact's honorific prefix, e.g. "Sir" *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: PHONETIC_GIVEN_NAME
variables.comment:
* The phonetic version of the given name for the contact. *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: PHONETIC_MIDDLE_NAME
variables.comment:
* The phonetic version of the additional name for the contact. *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: PHONETIC_FAMILY_NAME
variables.comment:
* The phonetic version of the family name for the contact. *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: FULL_NAME_STYLE
variables.comment:
* The style used for combining given/middle/family name into a full name.
             * See {@link ContactsContract.FullNameStyle}.

variables.name: PHONETIC_NAME_STYLE
variables.comment:
* The alphabet used for capturing the phonetic name.
             * See ContactsContract.PhoneticNameStyle.
